        "collapsed": true
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "516",
        "folderId": "393",
        "text": "Some parameters that affect the simulation as well as other static numbers."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "570",
        "folderId": "393",
        "text": "power: the power multiplier for a shot.\nwallcr: the coefficient of restitution (bounciness) for walls.\nballcr: the coefficient of restitution for 2 balls.\nfriction: a friction multiplier that slowly reduces the velocity each timestep.\nlaunchspeed: the minimum scalar speed the fastest ball can be traveling at to complete another shot."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "572",
        "folderId": "393",
        "text": "After that there's a whole bunch of sizes, and then there's:"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "573",
        "folderId": "393",
        "text": "s: the scaling factor from inches to Desmos screen units.\nstart: the starting point of the playing field (bottom left).\nend: the ending point (top right).\nfoot: the foot of the table, where the first ball is placed (right).\nhead: the head of the table, where the cue is placed (left).\nballidx: an array of all the ball indices.\npositions: an array of the default ball positions to reset to.\nzerovels: an array of velocities set to (0,0) to reset the balls velocities to.\nstripe: an array of ones and zeros representing which balls have stripes.\nstripesize: the size of the stripes.\npocketpos: an array of the positions of the pockets on the board.\npocketsize: the diameter of the pockets."
      },
