      {
        "type": "folder",
        "id": "375",
        "title": "Helper Functions",
        "collapsed": true
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "537",
        "folderId": "375",
        "text": "Some helpful functions to make the expressions a little bit more concise."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "538",
        "folderId": "375",
        "text": "A function to remove all the pesky undefined values from the list that my collision detection function outputs."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "287",
        "folderId": "375",
        "color": "#c74440",
        "latex": "r_{emovenan}\\left(l\\right)=l\\left[l=l\\right]"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "539",
        "folderId": "375",
        "text": "Normalize a vector (very intriguing)."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "335",
        "folderId": "375",
        "color": "#000000",
        "latex": "n_{orm}\\left(v\\right)=\\frac{v}{\\left|v\\right|}",
        "hidden": true
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "541",
        "folderId": "375",
        "text": "Offset a vector \"src\" in a direction \"angle\" by distance \"dist\"."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "112",
        "folderId": "375",
        "color": "#2d70b3",
        "latex": "o_{ffset}\\left(s_{rc},a_{ngle},d_{ist}\\right)=\\left(s_{rc}.x+d_{ist}\\cos\\left(a_{ngle}\\right),s_{rc}.y+d_{ist}\\sin\\left(a_{ngle}\\right)\\right)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "542",
        "folderId": "375",
        "text": "Batch collision detection used to detect if a vector is closer than a threshold \"detect\" to any point in a set."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "420",
        "folderId": "375",
        "color": "#c74440",
        "latex": "i_{ncircles}\\left(c_{ircles},d_{etect},p_{os}\\right)=\\min\\left(d_{istsqr}\\left(p_{os},c_{ircles}\\right)\\right)-d_{etect}^{2}"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "543",
        "folderId": "375",
        "text": "An atan2 helper function to make my other helper function \"angle\" more concise. It pretty much helps my helper function :]"
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "291",
        "folderId": "375",
        "color": "#000000",
        "latex": "a_{rctan2}\\left(x,y\\right)=\\left\\{x\\ge0:\\arctan\\left(\\frac{y}{x}\\right),xy\\le0:\\arctan\\left(\\frac{y}{x}\\right)+\\pi,\\ x<0:\\arctan\\left(\\frac{y}{x}\\right)-\\pi\\right\\}"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "544",
        "folderId": "375",
        "text": "The angle between two vectors"
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "147",
        "folderId": "375",
        "color": "#2d70b3",
        "latex": "a_{ngle}\\left(u,v\\right)=a_{rctan2}\\left(u.x-v.x,u.y-v.y\\right)-\\pi"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "545",
        "folderId": "375",
        "text": "The square of the distance between two points, because it's more efficient to compare this number to the square of a threshold when doing collision detection than to actually complete a square root to find the actual distance (computers hate doing square roots)!"
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "463",
        "folderId": "375",
        "color": "#388c46",
        "latex": "d_{istsqr}\\left(u,v\\right)=\\left(u.x-v.x\\right)^{2}+\\left(u.y-v.y\\right)^{2}"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "554",
        "folderId": "375",
        "text": "The star of the show! itemcollisions finds any balls that collide with any other balls"
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "155",
        "folderId": "375",
        "color": "#000000",
        "latex": "i_{temcollisions}\\left(i_{dx}\\right)=\\left[\\left\\{v_{isible}\\left[i_{dx}\\right]+v_{isible}\\left[c_{heckidx}\\right]=2:\\left\\{\\left|i_{dx}-c_{heckidx}\\right|>0:\\left\\{d_{istsqr}\\left(\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i_{dx}\\right],\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[c_{heckidx}\\right]\\right)<\\left(2b_{all}\\right)^{2}:c_{heckidx}\\right\\}\\right\\}\\right\\}\\operatorname{for}c_{heckidx}=\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allidx},16\\right)\\right]",
        "hidden": true
      },
      {
        "type": "folder",
        "id": "380",
        "title": "Velocity Calculation",
        "collapsed": true
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "546",
        "folderId": "380",
        "text": "Some functions used to update the velocity of the balls."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "547",
        "folderId": "380",
        "text": "A function to calculate the final velocity of an elastic collision from the two colliding velocities and positions."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "334",
        "folderId": "380",
        "color": "#6042a6",
        "latex": "f_{inalvel}\\left(v_{1},v_{2},p_{1},p_{2}\\right)=v_{1}-\\left(\\left(v_{1}-v_{2}\\right)\\cdot n_{orm}\\left(p_{1}-p_{2}\\right)\\right)n_{orm}\\left(p_{1}-p_{2}\\right)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "548",
        "folderId": "380",
        "text": "bouncepoints is wrapper for finalvel that ignores undefined values and also takes array indices as an input."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "317",
        "folderId": "380",
        "color": "#000000",
        "latex": "b_{ouncepoints}\\left(i_{dx1},i_{dx2}\\right)=\\left\\{i_{dx2}=i_{dx2}:b_{allcr}f_{inalvel}\\left(\\operatorname{join}\\left(v_{els},c_{uevel}\\right)\\left[i_{dx1}\\right],\\operatorname{join}\\left(v_{els},c_{uevel}\\right)\\left[i_{dx2}\\right],\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i_{dx1}\\right],\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i_{dx2}\\right]\\right),\\operatorname{join}\\left(v_{els},c_{uevel}\\right)\\left[i_{dx1}\\right]\\right\\}"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "549",
        "folderId": "380",
        "text": "bounceballs is a wrapper for bouncepoints that feeds it collisions."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "316",
        "folderId": "380",
        "color": "#6042a6",
        "latex": "b_{ounceballs}\\left(i_{dx}\\right)=b_{ouncepoints}\\left(i_{dx},r_{emovenan}\\left(i_{temcollisions}\\left(i_{dx}\\right)\\right)\\left[1\\right]\\right)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "550",
        "folderId": "380",
        "text": "This function takes in a velocity and mirrors it if the ball is colliding with a wall."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "126",
        "folderId": "380",
        "color": "#c74440",
        "latex": "b_{ouncewall}\\left(p_{os},v_{el}\\right)=\\left(\\left\\{p_{os}.x-b_{all}<s_{tart}.x:\\left\\{v_{el}.x<0:-w_{allcr}v_{el}.x,v_{el}.x\\right\\},\\left\\{p_{os}.x+b_{all}>e_{nd}.x:\\left\\{v_{el}.x>0:-w_{allcr}v_{el}.x,v_{el}.x\\right\\},v_{el}.x\\right\\}\\right\\},\\left\\{p_{os}.y-b_{all}<s_{tart}.y:\\left\\{v_{el}.y<0:-w_{allcr}v_{el}.y,v_{el}.y\\right\\},\\left\\{p_{os}.y+b_{all}>e_{nd}.y:\\left\\{v_{el}.y>0:-w_{allcr}v_{el}.y,v_{el}.y\\right\\},v_{el}.y\\right\\}\\right\\}\\right)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "551",
        "folderId": "380",
        "text": "A general function the applies all of the above functions as well as friction onto any position and array index."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "130",
        "folderId": "380",
        "color": "#000000",
        "latex": "c_{omputevel}\\left(p_{os},i_{dx}\\right)=f_{riction}b_{ouncewall}\\left(p_{os},b_{ounceballs}\\left(i_{dx}\\right)\\right)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "552",
        "folderId": "380",
        "text": "An action that uses computevel to update the velocities of all the balls."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "124",
        "folderId": "380",
        "color": "#6042a6",
        "latex": "u_{pdatevel}=v_{els}\\to\\left[c_{omputevel}\\left(b_{allpos}\\left[i_{dx}\\right],i_{dx}\\right)\\operatorname{for}i_{dx}=b_{allidx}\\right],c_{uevel}\\to\\left\\{i_{ncircles}\\left(p_{ocketpos},3b_{all},c_{ue}\\right)>0:c_{omputevel}\\left(c_{ue},16\\right),\\left(0,0\\right)\\right\\}"
      },
      {
        "type": "folder",
        "id": "381",
        "title": "Position Calculation",
        "collapsed": true
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "553",
        "folderId": "381",
        "text": "Some functions used to update the position of the balls."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "555",
        "folderId": "381",
        "text": "movepoint moves two balls away from eachother until they no longer collide."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "146",
        "folderId": "381",
        "color": "#c74440",
        "latex": "m_{ovepoint}\\left(i\\right)=\\left\\{d_{istsqr}\\left(\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i.x\\right],\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i.y\\right]\\right)<\\left(2b_{all}\\right)^{2}:o_{ffset}\\left(\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i.x\\right],a_{ngle}\\left(\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i.x\\right],\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i.y\\right]\\right),d_{istsqr}\\left(\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i.x\\right],\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i.y\\right]\\right)-\\left(2b_{all}\\right)^{2}-0.001\\right),\\operatorname{join}\\left(b_{allpos},c_{ue}\\right)\\left[i.x\\right]\\right\\}"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "556",
        "folderId": "381",
        "text": "fixcollisions uses movepoint to push apart any colliding balls."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "150",
        "folderId": "381",
        "color": "#000000",
        "latex": "f_{ixcollisions}\\left(i_{dx}\\right)=m_{ovepoint}\\left(\\left(i_{dx},r_{emovenan}\\left(i_{temcollisions}\\left(i_{dx}\\right)\\right)\\left[1\\right]\\right)\\right)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "557",
        "folderId": "381",
        "text": "updatepos is an action that uses fixcollisions to update the positions of all the balls as well as using euler integration to move the points in the direction of their velocity."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "122",
        "folderId": "381",
        "color": "#2d70b3",
        "latex": "u_{pdatepos}=b_{allpos}\\to\\left[f_{ixcollisions}\\left(i_{dx}\\right)\\operatorname{for}i_{dx}=b_{allidx}\\right]+v_{els},c_{ue}\\to\\left\\{i_{ncircles}\\left(p_{ocketpos},3b_{all},c_{ue}\\right)>0:f_{ixcollisions}\\left(16\\right)+c_{uevel},h_{ead}\\right\\}"
      },
      {
        "type": "folder",
        "id": "424",
        "title": "Logic",
        "collapsed": true
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "558",
        "folderId": "424",
        "text": "Logic functions and variables used for general game logic."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "559",
        "folderId": "424",
        "text": "updatevisible checks that no balls are touching a pocket, and makes them invisible if they are."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "426",
        "folderId": "424",
        "color": "#000000",
        "latex": "u_{pdatevisible}=v_{isible}\\to\\left[\\left\\{v_{isible}\\left[i_{dx}\\right]=1:\\left\\{i_{ncircles}\\left(p_{ocketpos},3b_{all},b_{allpos}\\left[i_{dx}\\right]\\right)<0:0,1\\right\\},0\\right\\}\\operatorname{for}i_{dx}=\\left[1...16\\right]\\right]"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "560",
        "folderId": "424",
        "text": "canlaunch is just a variable that contains the scalar speed of the fastest ball, and this checks against the \"launchspeed\" variable to determine if all the balls are slow enough for another shot to commence."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "487",
        "folderId": "424",
        "color": "#388c46",
        "latex": "c_{anlaunch}=\\max\\left(\\left|\\operatorname{join}\\left(v_{els},c_{uevel}\\right)\\right|\\right)"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "561",
        "folderId": "424",
        "text": "solidscore and stripescore are variables that basically find the sum of the bitwise and between the visible and solid/stripe balls to determine how many of each kind remain."
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "492",
        "folderId": "424",
        "color": "#388c46",
        "latex": "s_{olidscore}=\\left(\\sum_{n=1}^{16}\\left(\\left(1-s_{tripe}\\left[n\\right]\\right)v_{isible}\\left[n\\right]\\right)\\right)-1-v_{isible}\\left[8\\right]"
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "493",
        "folderId": "424",
        "color": "#6042a6",
        "latex": "s_{tripescore}=\\sum_{n=1}^{16}\\left(s_{tripe}\\left[n\\right]v_{isible}\\left[n\\right]\\right)"
      },
      {
        "type": "folder",
        "id": "394",
        "title": "Simulation Variables",
        "collapsed": true
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "562",
        "folderId": "394",
        "text": "These are variables that contain general live-updating information about the simulation, such as position and velocity. To minimize lag, close this folder (others too, but especially this one) when running the simulation."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "563",
        "folderId": "394",
        "text": "Cue position"
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "80",
        "folderId": "394",
        "color": "#388c46",
        "latex": "c_{ue}=\\left(-2.8125,0\\right)",
        "hidden": true
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "id": "564",
        "folderId": "394",
        "text": "Array of ball positions"
      },
      {
        "type": "expression",
        "id": "97",
